Exercises

    1. Flexible model better as more n wouldnt likely drastically change \(\hat{f}\) (low variance) and less flexible models may have too much bias
    2. Less flexible model better as less likely to overfit (less likely to have high variance)
    3. Flexible model better as more likely to have low bias
    4. Less flexible model better as less likely to overfit the high error terms
    1. Regression, inference, n=500, p=3
    2. Classification, prediction, n=20, p=13
    3. Regression, prediction, n=52, p=3
